<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 499th Homer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit his 499th career home run, and  
tied Sammy Sosa for the major league lead with 42 homers this year, 
in the seventh inning Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a 1-0 pitch from San Diego reliever Donne Wall an  
estimated 436 feet, a drive that cleared the left-field bullpen. 
The homer lifted the St. Louis Cardinals into a 6-all tie with the 
Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier in the day, Sosa homered for the Cubs against Montreal.  
</P>
<P>
	McGwire and Sosa have homered on the same day 35 times the last  
two seasons, including 15 times this year. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire leads the NL with 99 RBIs, including 11 in the last six  
games. He was 2-for-4 with a bases-loaded infield hit in the third, 
a popup and a strikeout. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
