<HEADLINE> Convicted Killer Executed in Texas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- A man who killed another man by hacking  
him to death with a sword made from a steel sawmill blade was 
executed by injection Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ricky Blackmon, 41, was the first of six Texas death row inmates  
expected to receive lethal injection over the next two weeks. He 
was the 17th put to death so far this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm happy, honestly happy,'' Blackmon said in a recent  
interview. ``God has said to me: `Ricky, this is your ticket home.' 
And I'm going home.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Blackmon was sentenced to death for killing Carl Rinkle, 26, at  
Rinkle's home in east Texas in March 1987, and taking more than 
$600 in cash, a small pistol, some jewelry and cowboy boots. 
</P>
<P>
	The murder weapon was a sawtooth-edge steel sword. Rinkle's  
skull and throat were slashed, and he was stabbed 21 times in the 
back with a large hunting knife. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
