<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lightning, Sharks Swap Five Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Lightning traded left wing  
Niklas Sundstrom to the San Jose Sharks on Wednesday in a 
five-player trade. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay sent Sundstrom and a third round draft pick to San  
Jose for defensemen Andrei Zyuzin and Bill Houlder and left wings 
Shawn Burr and Steve Guolla. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel we are a significantly better team today than we were  
yesterday,'' said Rick Dudley, the Lightning's vice president and 
general manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``Zyuzin is one of the most dynamic young defensemen in the  
league, Houlder immediately fills our need for a veteran 
defenseman, Burr is a proven character player in this league and 
Guolla has shown the ability to become a regular at the NHL 
level,'' Dudley said. 
</P>
<P>
	Sundstrom was acquired by the Lightning during the NHL draft in  
June from the New York Rangers along with goaltender Dan Cloutier 
and the Rangers' first- and third-round picks in the 2000 draft. 
The Lightning sent the fourth overall pick in this year's draft to 
New York. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers' third-round pick was dealt to San Jose Wednesday  
along with Sundstrom. 
</P>
<P>
	Sundstrom, 24, had 13 goals and 30 assists in 81 games with the  
Rangers last season. He scored 65 goals and had 98 assists in his 
four-year career with New York. 
</P>
<P>
	Zyuzin, 21, was the No. 2 pick in the 1996 NHL draft. The 6-1,  
200-pound Russian has played in 81 combined games the last two 
seasons, scoring nine and adding eight assists. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lightning re-acquired Houlder and Burr from the Sharks. Each  
played the 1995-96 and 1996-97 seasons with Tampa Bay before going 
to San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
	Houlder, 32, has played 12 NHL seasons with 50 goals and 153  
assists in 530 games. He led San Jose defensemen in scoring the 
last two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	In 874 games, the 33-year-old Burr has 181 goals and 257 assists  
but only had one point in 18 games last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Guolla, 26, played 64 games over the last three seasons. He  
scored 16 goals and had 11 assists. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
