<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Miami Heat Signs Otis Thorpe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Otis Thorpe, the 16th player in NBA history with  
15,000 points and 10,000 rebounds, signed a contract with the Miami 
Heat on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Thorpe, a free agent, averaged 11.3 points and 6.8 rebounds in  
49 games last season with the Washington Wizards. 
</P>
<P>
	``By acquiring Otis Thorpe, we have taken care of our first  
priority by fortifying our front line,'' Heat coach Pat Riley said 
in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	``Last year, our rebounding was one of the primary reasons we  
did not advance. We had to rectify it. In Otis Thorpe, we have a 
quality power forward-center who can rebound, defend and score,'' 
Riley said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-10 Thorpe played on the 1994 NBA champion Houston  
Rockets. 
</P>
<P>
	Over a 15-year NBA career, Thorpe's has averaged 14.9 points and  
8.7 rebounds during stops with Sacramento, Houston, Portland, 
Detroit, Vancouver and Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms weren't disclosed.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
