<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bengals Bring in Steelers' Castoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GEORGETOWN, Ky. (AP) -- Poor conditioning and extra weight got  
Jamain Stephens run out of Pittsburgh. Cincinnati Bengals coach 
Bruce Coslet, however, is happy to have the former first-round 
pick's bulk on his offensive line. 
</P>
<P>
	Waived Friday by the Steelers after failing to complete a set of  
40-yard runs on the opening day of training camp, Stephens was back 
on the field Wednesday for his first practice as a Bengal. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a big man, and those big guys are hard to find,'' Coslet  
said of the offensive tackle. ``He's played in the league. We're 
looking to improve ourselves.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stephens said he is ready to put his Pittsburgh experience  
behind him. 
</P>
<P>
	``It feels good,'' he said. ``I've got a fresh start, a new  
beginning, a new environment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stephens said he currently weighs over 350 pounds, and needs to  
lose at least 20 pounds to get down to his normal playing weight. 
</P>
<P>
	``I lose weight pretty easily,'' he said. ``I'll probably drop  
three or four pounds just today.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Coslet isn't convinced Stephens needs to slim down.  
</P>
<P>
	``He could stand to lose a little, but he's a big man. He  
doesn't look too sloppy to me,'' he said. ``We don't arbitrarily 
assign weight. We'll watch him work out and then make some 
suggestions if need be.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The North Carolina A&AMP;T product was the 29th player taken in the  
1996 draft, but struggled with weight problems throughout his 
Pittsburgh tenure. 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, there were questions whether Stephens would survive  
the Steelers' final roster cutdown, but he went on to start 10 
games when the offensive line was hit by injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	``There was controversy from day one,'' Stephens said of his  
three seasons in Pittsburgh. ``The ice never broke for me there. 
... I have no hard feelings against coach Cowher or the whole 
Steelers organization. They were nothing but patient with me the 
whole time I was there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stephens blamed his July 3 wedding for causing his conditioning  
to slip during the last month. 
</P>
<P>
	``I kind of honeymooned a little longer than I should have,'' he  
said. ``I lost focus. I started feeling sorry for myself.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
