<HEADLINE> Gwynn Now Has 2,998 Hits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Tony Gwynn hit his third career grand slam and  
two singles in his first four at-bats Wednesday night, giving him 
2,998 career hits. 
</P>
<P>
	Gwynn had been 1-for-9 the first two games of the series and  
entered the game 13-for-57 (.228) since being activated from the 
disabled list July 19. The stretch had dropped his average to .309, 
30 points below his career average. 
</P>
<P>
	After fouling out in the first, Gwynn singled and scored on  
Reggie Sanders' home run in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	Gwynn hit his fifth homer of the season off Kent Mercker's first  
pitch with two outs in the fifth to put the Padres ahead 6-3. His 
last grand slam was June 26, 1997, an inside-the-park homer at Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	Gwynn singled in the seventh off Mike Mohler.  
  	   	
</P>
