<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Meningitis Hospitalizes Jerry Lewis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Jerry Lewis is ``doing fine'' following a bout  
with viral meningitis and will be ready to host his annual Labor 
Day Telethon next month, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's had a miserable week and will likely be spending some  
time on his boat for some r-and-r,'' executive assistant Claudia 
Stabile said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis, 73, was hospitalized in Darwin, Australia, earlier this  
week after falling ill Sunday during a performance tour. 
</P>
<P>
	He had hoped to resume performances today in Sydney, but the  
decision was made to cancel the balance of the tour and return 
home. Lewis was described as feeling fine, but not well enough to 
perform. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis lives in Las Vegas with his wife and daughter. He is  
expected to fly home in the next few days, Stabile said. 
</P>
<P>
	The illness will not impact Lewis' role in the annual Los  
Angeles-based Labor Day Telethon for the Muscular Dystrophy 
Association, Stabile said. 
  	   	
</P>
