<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hutchinson Technology To Cut Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUTCHINSON, Minn. (AP) -- Hutchinson Technology Inc. will cut 500  
jobs at its plant here and increase employment at plants in South 
Dakota and Wisconsin as it consolidates some manufacturing 
operations, the company said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	To improve efficiency and cut costs, assembly operations now  
based in Hutchinson will be transferred to the company's plants in 
Eau Claire, Wis., and Sioux Falls, S.D., the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hutchinson Technology is the leading worldwide supplier of  
suspension assemblies for computer disk drives, which supports the 
mechanism that allows users to read from and write to the hard 
drive. 
</P>
<P>
	The job cuts represent a little more than 6 percent of  
Hutchinson's 8,000-member work force. 
</P>
<P>
	Employees whose jobs are eliminated will be offered severance  
packages and help in finding new jobs. The company also said it 
will offer relocation assistance to Hutchinson employees interested 
in jobs that become available at the company's other plants. 
</P>
<P>
	Hutchinson Technology will take a charge in its fiscal fourth  
quarter ending Sept. 26 to cover the consolidation. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
