<HEADLINE> Singer Gans Signs Mirage Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Entertainer Danny Gans remembers moving here  
three years ago, dreaming of headlining on the Las Vegas Strip. 
</P>
<P>
	That dream was realized Tuesday when it was announced that Gans  
had signed an eight-year, multimillion-dollar contract with Mirage 
Resorts Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	``I stand before you as proof that dreams do come true,'' Gans  
said at a news conference. 
</P>
<P>
	Gans has been the headliner at the Rio Suite Hotel and Casino  
since January 1997. The Mirage announcement comes just days after 
former teen idol David Cassidy was named as the Rio's new 
headliner. 
</P>
<P>
	Plans call for Gans to debut at the Mirage on April 1. The  
financial terms of his contract were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	Gans is scheduled to release a new CD of Christian pop music in  
February. The filming of a Gans TV sitcom pilot, set in Las Vegas 
and produced by Aaron Spelling, was delayed until the fall of 2000 
to allow him to get settled at The Mirage. 


  	   	
</P>
