<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Move Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was lower in European trading  
Wednesday. Gold prices also fell. Later, in midday trading in New 
York, the euro traded at $1.0765. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0767, up from $1.0648 Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Tuesday: 114.23 Japanese  
yen, down from 115.20; 1.4846 Swiss francs, down from 1.5006; and 
1.4922 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4962 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6228, up from $1.6161.  
</P>
<P>
	Midday in New York, the dollar bought 114.22 yen, and the pound  
was worth $1.5635. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8165 German marks, down from 1.8368; 
