<HEADLINE> Jerry Lewis Cancels Australian Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Comedian Jerry Lewis has canceled the  
remaining shows on his Australian tour after falling ill with viral 
meningitis, a spokeswoman said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis, 73, was hospitalized in the northern city of Darwin  
earlier this week after falling ill on Sunday, said the spokeswoman 
for the Australian tour promoter on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	He had hoped to restart his Australia-wide tour on Thursday in  
Sydney, she said. 
</P>
<P>
	``He'll be fine ... he's just not well enough to perform,'' the  
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis planned to fly home to the United States in the next few  
days, she said. 
  	   	
</P>
