<HEADLINE> Lions Sign QB Hollas, Let Go Powlus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIVERSITY CENTER, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Lions released  
quarterback Ron Powlus on Wednesday to make room for newcomer 
Donald Hollas, a former quarterack for the Oakland Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
	Powlus joined the Lions roughly six months ago as a free agent  
but was let go in a move Lions coach Bobby Ross called ``a tough 
thing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``We wanted to take a good look at Powlus,'' Ross said at the  
Lions' camp at Saginaw Valley State. ``I don't want five QB's out 
here. I wanted four, so we had to make that decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``Now that we have Don Hollas in, he has to do a lot of catching  
up,'' Ross said of the newcomer who spent his first day in 
Detroit's camp. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lions corps of quarterbacks also includes starter Charlie  
Batch, Gus Frerotte and Corey Sauter. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Raiders last season, Hollas completed 135 of 260 passes  
for 1,754 yards. He threw 10 touchdowns and 16 interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
	Powlus, who has never thrown an NFL regular-season pass, tossed  
for 121 yards in two preseason games for the relocated Tennessee 
franchise last year. During the final two weeks of last season, he 
was with the St. Louis Rams' practice squad. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
