<HEADLINE> Share Prices Mixed in Europe Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Share prices were mixed on European stock  
exchanges Wednesday as rising steel stocks were offset by a drop in 
some technology and telecommunications shares. 
</P>
<P>
	Dealers said steel shares were buoyed by hopes of a price  
increase and by news that plans for a merger between British Steel 
and Amsterdam-based steel manufacturer Hoogovens are on track. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Basic Resources index was the best performer on  
the day, with a gain of 2.3 percent, as British Steel shares rose 4 
pence to 170.45 pence and Hoogovens shares rose 1.80 euros to 56.70 
euros. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in  
countries that have joined the single currency, closed down 0.99 
points at 309.43. The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 23.36 
points to 3590.69, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed down 24.10 
points at 3585.82. 
</P>
<P>
	BASF led chemical stocks higher on merger speculation. The stock  
gained 5.3 percent, or 2.26 euros, to close at 44.74 euros, as a 
merger between Dow Chemical and Union Carbide prompted talk of 
further tie-ups, and lifted the Dow Jones Industrial Average as 
much as 152.60 points, or 1.4 percent, to 10,829.91 at the opening. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement will create the world's second-largest chemical  
group, with combined annual revenues of $24 billion a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Chemical index closed up 1.7 percent, making it  
the second-best performer on the day. Other chemical shares that 
rose included Bayer, up 86 cents at 41.30 euros, and ICI, up 9 
pence at 752 pence. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paris CAC-40 index fell 0.7 percent to 4326.20, with shares  
of Banque Nationale de Paris, Societe Generale and Paribas down on 
concern that a protracted takeover battle may end with BNP gaining 
control of Paribas, but not Societe Generale. 
</P>
<P>
	Milan's MIBtel index fell 0.6 percent to 32,534, while  
Amsterdam's AEX index rose 0.1 percent to 540.68. London's 
Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed down 0.2 
percent at 6,235.4. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares in British Telecommunications PLC fell 46 pence to 986  
pence on reports that rival Telewest Communications is expected to 
launch a high-speed Internet service. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
