<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Giants Place Kent on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Jeff Kent, who missed seven games with the San  
Francisco Giants because of inflammation in his left foot, was 
placed on the 15-day disabled list Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kent returned Monday night in the series opener against the  
Arizona Diamondbacks, going 2-for-4 with an RBI in San Francisco's 
16-6 loss. But Kent was on the bench again Tuesday night as the 
pain worsened. 
</P>
<P>
	Kent flew back to San Francisco on Wednesday and was examined by  
foot specialist Dr. Larry Oloff, who placed the foot in a 
weight-bearing cast. Kent will be eligible to come off the disabled 
list on Aug. 18. 
</P>
<P>
	Kent had been bothered by the injury since early in the season  
but still was selected to the All-Star game for the first time in 
his career. He is hitting .292 with 64 RBIs and 13 home runs. 
</P>
<P>
	Kent was bothered by a similar problem in his right foot last  
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramon Martinez has started three of the last four games at short  
for the Giants after being recalled from Triple-A Fresno on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	By placing Kent on the DL, the Giants did not have to make  
another roster move to make room for right-handed pitcher Joe 
Nathan, who started Wednesday against Arizona after being recalled 
from Fresno. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
