<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that have been moving substantially or  
trading heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq 
Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Union Carbide Corp., up 10 5/8 at 59 7/16  
</P>
<P>
 *Dow Chemical Co., down 6 5/16 at 118 3/8 
</P>
<P>
	Dow Chemical Co. is buying Union Carbide for $9.3 billion in  
stock, creating the world's second-largest chemical company behind 
DuPont. About 2,000 jobs will be cut, and the companies said they 
expect the deal to save a combined $500 million a year. 

</P>
<P>
 *American Medical Security Group Inc., down 13/16 at 10 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, which sells health care benefits and insurance  
products, lost 21 cents per share in the second quarter, compared 
to a gain of 7 cents per share in last year's second quarter. The 
company's board approved the repurchase up to $10 million in stock. 

</P>
<P>
 *Burns International Services Corp., down 1 15/16 at 17    	
</P>
<P>
	Burns said talks of a business combination with another company  
have been terminated. Burns, which previously operated as 
Borg-Warner Security Corp., had received an ``unsolicited 
preliminary indication of interest'' for a business combination. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Diatide Inc., up 5/8 at 6 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Diatide, based in Londonderry, N.H., received approval from the  
Food and Drug Administration to market its NeoTect imaging agent 
for use in detecting malignant lung tumors. 

</P>
<P>
 *Staples Inc., down 3 1/16 at 23 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	An analyst at Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette downgraded Staples  
stock from ``buy'' to ``market perform.'' The analyst also lowered 
his rating on competitors Office Depot Inc. and Officemax Inc. 

</P>
<P>
 *First Sierra Financial, down 4 13/16 at 12 11/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, which provides electronic commerce technology and  
services to small businesses, earned 2 cents per share in the 
second quarter, compared to 11 cents per share in the second 
quarter of 1998. 

</P>
<P>
 *Condor Technology, down 2 5/32 at 2 9/32    	
</P>
<P>
	Condor, which makes enterprise portal systems, had an operating  
loss of 5 cents per share in the second quarter, compared with a 
gain of 18 cents a share in last year's second quarter. The company 
expects restructuring charges of $500,000 to $1.5 million in the 
third quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Superconductor Technologies Inc., down 1 1/8 to 2 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The company widened its losses in the second quarter to 31 cents  
per share from 28 cents per share in the second quarter of 1998. 
Separately, Chief Financial Officer James Evans resigned to pursue 
other interests. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
