<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	Halle Berry says Hollywood isn't ready for a black leading lady.  
She reached that conclusion after starring in the new HBO movie 
``Introducing Dorothy Dandridge,'' about the first black woman 
nominated for an Oscar as best actress. ``For the last six months, 
I have not been able to find a project that can even compare to the 
role that I've just been able to play, so that's how I'm sure 
there's no place for a black leading lady right now,'' she said. 
Berry was born on Aug. 14, 1968. 

</P>
<P>
	Dustin Hoffman, born Aug. 8, 1937, is co-producer of ``A Walk on  
the Moon.'' The film is about life in a Jewish vacation spot in the 
Catskills in the summer of 1969. Liev Schreiber and Diane Lane play 
a working-class New York couple who get caught up in the times. 

</P>
<P>
	Singer Whitney Houston, born Aug. 9, 1963, is among the nominees  
for the 1999 MTV Video Music Awards. Houston is nominated in the 
R&AMP;B Video category for ``Heartbreak Hotel,'' featuring Faith Evans 
and Kelly Price. The awards will be presented in New York on Sept. 
9. 

</P>
